@Mean Old Lady

When I lived in Japan I needed a Phillips head screwdriver. I had pretty good conversational Japanese (thanks, Grandma!) but for western-style goods Japanese often use their own version of English rather than a native term, so at the local-and-pop hardware store I asked for a “huirripsu doraibaa.” (Japanese does not have a real “f” or “v” sound, and virtually all syllables end with a vowel.) I was met with a puzzled look, so I tried again. Finally I drew a rudimentary picture. “Ah! Purassu doraibaa!”

(A “plus” driver. I then learned that a standard screwdriver is a “minus” driver. Both of which I thought were far more sensible than “Phillips” and “standard.”)

